<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-83807">
<article id="comment-83807" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c6460822d85db8c3d9996008126960ce?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c6460822d85db8c3d9996008126960ce?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">Camille</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/best-cat-brush#comment-83807"><time datetime="2022-06-29T05:07:37+00:00">Jun 29, 2022 at 5:07 am</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>I really like SleekEZ. It’s really effective at removing the undercoat and yet super gentle. My med-long hair love bug didn’t do well with the furminator (seemed too uncomfortable) or and the boars hair brush didn’t seem to be too effective. He purrs and looks like he’s ready to sleep when I use this on him, but there are piles of fur that come off him. And he looks so clean and well groomed after I use it. I guess lots of folks use the bigger versions on horses and dogs.</p>
</section>
