<article id="comment-84597" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='small mallory photo' src='https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cropped-Small-pfp-44x44.jpg' srcset='https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cropped-Small-pfp-88x88.jpg 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn"><a href='https://www.wildernesscat.com/' rel='external nofollow ugc' class='url'>Mallory Crusta</a></b> <span>Post author</span></cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/best-cat-brush#comment-84597"><time datetime="2022-07-14T15:48:24+00:00">Jul 14, 2022 at 3:48 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>Hey Marissa, it&#8217;s wonderful that you&#8217;re caring for your arthritic cat&#8217;s coat. I would think that a brush glove would be the gentlest option for an arthritic kitty. Are you also using any supplements? I&#8217;ve heard good things about omega-3 supplements for inflammation relief—a good fish oil could help your cat in terms of both joint and coat health.</p>
</section>
